  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Agriculture Aquaculture Fish Health Surveillance\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Agriculture Aquaculture Fish Health Surveillance\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Agriculture domain machine for aquaculture operations focused on fish health surveillance. It monitors behavior, mortality trend, lesion observations, and treatment routing and emits AI-dispatchable outputs at [76:80] for automation, maintenance, and optimization workflows.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- process_stability_norm (index 0):  0.0 = unstable or outside safe operating band; | 0.5 = watch band; | 1.0 = stable in target band\n- resource_efficiency_norm (index 1):  0.0 = wasteful or constrained; | 0.5 = acceptable; | 1.0 = efficient and available\n- biosecurity_or_ipm_norm (index 2):  0.0 = active biological threat; | 0.5 = mitigated watch state; | 1.0 = controlled and documented\n- maintenance_readiness_norm (index 3):  0.0 = overdue or faulted; | 0.5 = service due soon; | 1.0 = maintained and verified\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- agx-007-urgent-stabilize (RED) -> action: Dispatch growhouse_irrigation_agent to stabilize fish health surveillance and record corrective action.\n- agx-007-optimize-operation (GREEN) -> action: Run AI optimization for fish health surveillance using the latest operating window and production targets.\n- agx-007-preventive-maintenance (GREEN) -> action: Create preventive-maintenance work for fish health surveillance and verify completion telemetry.\n- agx-007-operating-window-ok (GREEN) -> action: Continue automated monitoring for fish health surveillance while preserving current setpoints.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "process_stability_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "unstable or outside safe operating band;",
          "mid": "watch band;",
          "high": "stable in target band"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "resource_efficiency_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "wasteful or constrained;",
          "mid": "acceptable;",
          "high": "efficient and available"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "biosecurity_or_ipm_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "active biological threat;",
          "mid": "mitigated watch state;",
          "high": "controlled and documented"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "maintenance_readiness_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "overdue or faulted;",
          "mid": "service due soon;",
          "high": "maintained and verified"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "agx-007-urgent-stabilize",
        "label": "agx-007-urgent-stabilize",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Dispatch growhouse_irrigation_agent to stabilize fish health surveillance and record corrective action."
